# Verification: Manual Build Process

Because the standard `vite build` process consistently failed in this environment (likely due to memory constraints or system configuration issues), I implemented a **Manual Build Strategy**.

## Strategy Overview

Instead of pre-compiling the React code into a bundle, I configured the application to use **in-browser compilation** via `babel-standalone`.

1. **Dependency Management**: Downloaded `react`, `react-dom`, and `babel` libraries locally to `dist/lib` using `curl`.
2. **Structure**:
   - [dist/index.html](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/dist/index.html): Loads libraries and points to [src/main.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/main.jsx).
   - [dist/src/App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/dist/src/App.jsx): Contains the full application logic (consolidated into one file), modified to use global `React` object instead of imports.
   - [dist/src/main.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/dist/src/main.jsx): Entry point.
3. **Execution**:
   - `npx cap copy`: Copies `dist` to Android assets.
   - `npx cap sync`: Updates native project.
   - `gradlew assembleDebug`: Builds the APK.

